Armand Dutertre https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Armand_Dutertre 0 Armand Dutertre (17 July 1854 – 31 May 1932) was a French actor. He was born Bolesław Camille Plucinski in Lublin, Poland (then part of the Russian Empire) and died in Cannes, France. He was a resident at the Odéon-Théâtre de l'Europe in Paris, then manager of the Reims Theater from 1898 to 1899. He became professor at the Conservatory of Nice and was also film actor from 1913 to 1929. He was interred at the Cimetière du Grand Jas in Cannes.
